---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-hong-kong', text: 'Leaving Hong Kong Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'mpf-considerations', text: 'MPF Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best UK Expat Insurance', href: '/best/uk-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Canadian Expat Insurance', href: '/best/canadian-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Australian Expat Insurance', href: '/best/australian-expat-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'service', header: 'Service Quality' },
  { key: 'globalNetwork', header: 'Global Network' },
  { key: 'hkCoverage', header: 'HK Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', service: 'Excellent', globalNetwork: 'Excellent', hkCoverage: 'Add-on (expensive)', price: 'HKD 2,500/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', service: 'Premium', globalNetwork: 'Excellent', hkCoverage: 'Add-on (expensive)', price: 'HKD 2,800/mo' },
  { provider: 'AIA Hong Kong', service: 'Good', globalNetwork: 'Good', hkCoverage: 'Included', price: 'HKD 2,200/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', service: 'Very Good', globalNetwork: 'Strong', hkCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'HKD 2,300/mo' },
  { provider: 'AXA Hong Kong', service: 'Good', globalNetwork: 'Good', hkCoverage: 'Included', price: 'HKD 2,000/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Hong Kong Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Hong Kong expats. Find coverage for UK, Canada, Australia, and other destinations."
  headline="Best Insurance for Hong Kong Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Hong Kong has excellent healthcare, but emigrating means starting fresh. Here's how to stay covered in the UK, Canada, Australia, and beyond."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/hong-kong-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Hong Kong emigrants are concentrated in the UK, Canada, Australia, Taiwan, and other destinations. Understanding how to transition from Hong Kong's healthcare system is important. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Hong Kong expats. Strong networks worldwide, premium service matching HK expectations.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Top-tier coverage with excellent service. Bupa has strong HK presence.</li>
    <li><strong>AIA Hong Kong:</strong> Major HK insurer with international products. Familiar brand, includes HK coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good global coverage at competitive prices.</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Hong Kong:</strong> HK insurer offering international coverage. Familiar service.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Hong Kong Coverage Warning"
    description="Hong Kong healthcare is expensive. International policies that include HK coverage carry premium pricing. Consider whether you need HK coverage or can manage visits differently."
    buttonText="Compare Options"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-hong-kong">Leaving Hong Kong Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Hong Kong has excellent but expensive healthcare. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>Public Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    Hong Kong's public healthcare system provides subsidized care to Hong Kong ID holders. When you emigrate and give up your HKID, you lose access to public healthcare subsidies. Visits as a tourist mean paying full (expensive) private rates.
  </p>

  <h3>Private HK Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    If you have private health insurance through Hong Kong insurers (AIA, AXA, Bupa HK, Prudential), check whether it can continue abroad. Most policies are designed for Hong Kong residents—terms change when you emigrate.
  </p>

  <h3>Employer Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    If your coverage was through your Hong Kong employer, it ends when you leave employment. You need independent international insurance for your new destination.
  </p>

  <h3>VHIS (Voluntary Health Insurance Scheme)</h3>
  <p>
    VHIS policies are designed for Hong Kong residents. When you emigrate, these policies typically don't continue. International insurance replaces this coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="mpf-considerations">MPF Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    The Mandatory Provident Fund (MPF) is Hong Kong's retirement system:
  </p>

  <h3>MPF Withdrawal</h3>
  <p>
    Permanent departure from Hong Kong allows MPF withdrawal under certain conditions. You must provide evidence of permanent departure and make a statutory declaration.
  </p>

  <h3>MPF and Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    MPF is for retirement—it doesn't include healthcare coverage. You need separate health insurance regardless of your MPF decisions.
  </p>

  <h3>Tax Implications</h3>
  <p>
    Consider tax implications of MPF withdrawal in your new country of residence. This is a financial planning issue separate from healthcare coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Service Quality Expectations</h3>
  <p>
    Hong Kong residents are accustomed to excellent healthcare service. International insurance should match these expectations—fast claims, good hospitals, responsive service.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">BN(O) Visa Holders (UK)</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Many Hong Kong emigrants are using BN(O) visas to move to the UK. NHS provides free healthcare to UK residents. Private insurance supplements NHS with faster access and more choices.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers premium international coverage matching Hong Kong service expectations. Strong networks in the UK (popular BN(O) destination), Canada, Australia, and worldwide. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 service with Cantonese and English support. Hong Kong coverage can be added but is expensive due to HK healthcare costs.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Hong Kong expats who want premium coverage matching HK standards.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa has significant presence in Hong Kong and offers excellent global coverage. Premium positioning with outstanding service quality. Networks include top hospitals in all major HK emigration destinations.
  </p>

  <p>
    Familiar brand for Hong Kong residents. Hong Kong coverage available at additional cost.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Hong Kong expats who want premium coverage from a familiar brand.
  </p>

  <h3>AIA Hong Kong</h3>
  <p>
    AIA is one of Hong Kong's largest insurers and offers international products. Familiar brand, familiar processes, Hong Kong coverage included automatically.
  </p>

  <p>
    International networks are adequate, strongest in Asia-Pacific. Good option for those wanting continuity.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Hong Kong expats who prefer familiar HK service with seamless home coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in Europe (including UK) and adequate coverage elsewhere. Good value for comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Hong Kong expats seeking good value with strong UK/European coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>AXA Hong Kong</h3>
  <p>
    AXA has presence in Hong Kong and offers international products. Familiar brand, Hong Kong coverage included. Networks adequate for most destinations.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Hong Kong expats who prefer familiar HK service and want included home coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Premium Options"
    description="Hong Kong expats typically prioritize quality. Compare top-tier plans for your specific destination."
    buttonText="Get Premium Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Hong Kong emigrants have specific destination patterns:
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    Most popular destination for BN(O) visa holders. NHS provides free healthcare to residents. Many Hong Kong emigrants supplement NHS with private insurance for faster access, especially during NHS waiting list challenges.
  </p>

  <h3>Canada</h3>
  <p>
    Traditional Hong Kong emigration destination, especially Vancouver and Toronto. Provincial healthcare covers residents after waiting period (typically 3 months). International insurance covers the gap.
  </p>

  <h3>Australia</h3>
  <p>
    Popular destination, especially Sydney and Melbourne. Medicare covers permanent residents after waiting period. Private health insurance common in Australia for faster access.
  </p>

  <h3>Taiwan</h3>
  <p>
    Growing destination for Hong Kong emigrants. Taiwan's National Health Insurance covers legal residents. International insurance supplements local coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Can I keep my HK insurance abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Most HK policies are designed for residents. When you emigrate, terms change or policies cancel. Check with your specific insurer and plan for international coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is NHS enough in the UK?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">NHS provides comprehensive coverage for residents. However, waiting times can be long. Many HK emigrants supplement with private insurance for faster access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Should I withdraw MPF?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">This is a financial decision separate from healthcare. Permanent departure allows withdrawal. Healthcare requires separate insurance regardless of MPF decisions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is HK coverage expensive on international plans?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Yes. Hong Kong healthcare costs are high, making HK coverage expensive on international policies. Consider whether you need it or can manage HK visits differently.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is AIA or Cigna better?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">AIA offers HK familiarity and includes HK coverage. Cigna has stronger global networks. Choose based on destination and how important HK integration is.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about Cantonese support?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">HK insurers (AIA, AXA) offer Cantonese service. International insurers have varying Cantonese capability—Cigna and Bupa have some support through their HK operations.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Hong Kong expats need comprehensive international insurance—HK healthcare doesn't follow you abroad. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> and <strong>Bupa Global</strong> premium tiers match HK service expectations. <strong>AIA Hong Kong</strong> suits those who prefer familiar HK service.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offers good value for UK-bound expats. <strong>AXA Hong Kong</strong> works for those wanting familiar service with included HK coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    In the UK, NHS provides base coverage—private insurance supplements this. Plan your healthcare transition alongside your emigration planning.
  </p>

</PageShell>
